/bin/bash -lc "cat > docs/agents/reports/2026-03-05-phase11-codex.md <<'EOF'
COMPLETION REPORT
AGENT: codex
TASK: Implement Phase 11 WebSocket handlers and Phase 12 GCode tests
DATE: 2026-03-05
STATUS: done

## Files Changed
- created: internal/web/ws/common.go
- created: internal/web/ws/mqtt.go
- created: internal/web/ws/video.go
- created: internal/web/ws/pppp.go
- created: internal/web/ws/upload.go
- created: internal/web/ws/ctrl.go
- created: internal/web/ws/ws_test.go
- created: internal/gcode/gcode_test.go
- modified: internal/web/routes.go
- modified: internal/web/server.go
- modified: internal/service/pppp.go

## Decisions Made
- Implemented dedicated WebSocket handlers under "'`internal/web/ws` and wired them directly in `internal/web/routes.go`.
- Used gorilla/websocket read/write pump separation with ping/pong keepalive (`30s` ping, `60s` pong wait).
- For stream handlers (`/ws/mqtt`, `/ws/video`, `/ws/upload`), used buffered intermediary channels (`size 32`) and non-blocking Tap callbacks to avoid callback backpressure.
- `/ws/ctrl` enforces inline first-message auth (`api_key`) with `crypto/subtle.ConstantTimeCompare`, and closes with code `1008` on policy violations.
- `/ws/ctrl` command contract implemented as requested:
  - `{"cmd":"light","value":"on|off"}`
  - `{"cmd":"video_profile","value":"sd|hd|fhd"}`
  - `{"cmd":"video_enable","value":true|false}`
- Added `Server.VideoSupported()` so WS handlers can enforce printer camera capability checks.
- Added `PPPPService.IsConnected()` for `/ws/pppp-state` polling.
- Added table-driven GCode tests covering `PatchGCodeTime` and `ExtractLayerCount` scenarios from spec.

## Deviations from Spec
- `/ws/pppp-state` emits an initial status immediately on connect and then every 2 seconds; payload includes `service_state` when `ppppservice` is registered. This is additive and backward compatible.

## Known Issues / TODO
- none

## Open Questions for Review
- Should `/ws/ctrl` also emit initial `{"ankerctl":1}` / `{"video_profile":"..."}` connect messages for exact Python parity, or keep only auth + command responses?
- Should `/ws/pppp-state` status semantics be restricted to `connected|disconnected` only, or keep `dormant` when service is not running?

## Test Coverage
- covered: websocket handler behavior for `/ws/mqtt`, `/ws/video`, `/ws/pppp-state`, `/ws/upload`, `/ws/ctrl` (success + auth rejection); GCode time patching and layer extraction cases.
- not covered: end-to-end WS integration with real `MqttQueue`/`VideoQueue`/`PPPPService` runtime wiring and real network frames.
