codex
Implemented Phase 11 WS handlers and Phase 12 GCode tests, wired into routes, and verified with full build + race tests.

**What changed**
- Added WebSocket handler package implementation:
  - [common.go](/data_hdd/ankerctl_go_remake/internal/web/ws/common.go)
  - [mqtt.go](/data_hdd/ankerctl_go_remake/internal/web/ws/mqtt.go)
  - [video.go](/data_hdd/ankerctl_go_remake/internal/web/ws/video.go)
  - [pppp.go](/data_hdd/ankerctl_go_remake/internal/web/ws/pppp.go)
  - [upload.go](/data_hdd/ankerctl_go_remake/internal/web/ws/upload.go)
  - [ctrl.go](/data_hdd/ankerctl_go_remake/internal/web/ws/ctrl.go)
  - [ws_test.go](/data_hdd/ankerctl_go_remake/internal/web/ws/ws_test.go)

- Added GCode tests:
  - [gcode_test.go](/data_hdd/ankerctl_go_remake/internal/gcode/gcode_test.go)

- Wired WS routes from placeholders to real handlers:
  - [routes.go](/data_hdd/ankerctl_go_remake/internal/web/routes.go)

- Added server capability accessor used by WS layer:
  - [server.go](/data_hdd/ankerctl_go_remake/internal/web/server.go)

- Added PPPP connectivity accessor for `/ws/pppp-state` polling:
  - [pppp.go](/data_hdd/ankerctl_go_remake/internal/service/pppp.go)

**Spec-critical behavior implemented**
- `/ws/ctrl` inline auth on first message with `api_key`, constant-time compare, closes with code `1008` on missing/invalid key.
- `/ws/ctrl` commands:
  - `{"cmd":"light","value":"on|off"}`
  - `{"cmd":"video_profile","value":"sd|hd|fhd"}`
  - `{"cmd":"video_enable","value":true|false}`
- All WS handlers use read/write pump separation, ping/pong keepalive, context/disconnect cleanup.
- Tap callbacks are non-blocking via buffered channel (`size 32`) before write pump.
- GCode tests cover requested `PatchGCodeTime` and `ExtractLayerCount` cases.

**Verification**
Ran exactly:
- `go build ./...`
- `go test -race ./...`

Both passed.

**Report written**
- [2026-03-05-phase11-codex.md](/data_hdd/ankerctl_go_remake/docs/agents/reports/2026-03-05-phase11-codex.md)
